{"mode":"repetition","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Answer the following questions.<\/strong><\/p>\n","dialogs":[{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is an operating system?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>An operating system is a part of system software, which controls and coordinates overall functions of a computer.<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60f155ae9ef46.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":512,"height":512}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What acts as an interface between the software and the computer hardware?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\">An operating sytem<\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60f155084715a.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":483,"height":451}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What are some examples of popular operating systems?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Windows7,&nbsp;Windows10,&nbsp;Unix,&nbsp;Linux,&nbsp;Ms-DOS and more.<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60f156d26043f.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":640,"height":480}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>A function of OS is to allocate required memory to local the program and data into RAM. Is the given statement true?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Yes, it is true.<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60f15737ecd08.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":512,"height":512}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What part of OS allocates a processor to execute a chosen program?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Processor Management<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60f1596babe25.png","mime":"image